Welcome to Pivotal Cloud Foundry Documentation!

## <a id="about-pcf"></a> What is Pivotal Cloud Foundry?

Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF) is an enterprise platform for running and managing cloud-native apps and workloads. 

As a platform, PCF provides layers of abstraction in the form of runtimes. These abstraction layers allow operators to manage shared resources 
without exposing the complexity of those resources to developers who want to deliver software continuously on the platform.

PCF Operators manage the platform and its shared resources by using [Ops Manager](../customizing/ops-man.html).

Runtimes available in PCF are the following:

* [Pivotal Application Service (PAS)](../customizing/configure-pas.html)
* [Enterprise Pivotal Container Service (Enterprise PKS)](https://docs.pivotal.io/runtimes/pks)
* [Pivotal Function Service (PFS)](https://docs.pivotal.io/pfs/)

